item.title: Amazon’s brilliant plan to pay you crazy money for your iPad 2
item.description: Amazon's brilliant plan to pay you crazy money for your iPad 2 http://t.co/Srd7r7gk
item.content:encoded: Amazon's brilliant plan to pay you crazy money for your iPad 2 http://t.co/Srd7r7gk It’s been three days since Tim Cook unveiled the new iPad, but you’re still stuck with your trusty old iPad 2. You’re keen to get rid of it so you can buy the new one, but you forgot to log in to one of those buy-back sites before Wednesday’s launch. Predictably, the announcement sent trade-in values plummeting—before the launch, some of these sites were offering close to $300 for your entry-level iPad 2 (the 16GB Wi-Fi model), provided it was in “good” condition. Now they’re willing to part with far less: As of Saturday morning, if you’ve got a well-cared-for iPad 2, NextWorth will give you $241 for it. BuyBackMac is offering $224. eBay’s Instant Sale will net you $200. And Gazelle, the most popular of the buy-back sites, will only part with $185. Link - Trackbacks

item.content:encoded: .@JetBlue boots family off flight because of toddler's tantrum http://t.co/vuwv6i16 Read 'Toddler Tantrum Gets Family Booted from JetBlue Flight. Is Flying Still Kid-friendly?' from our blog Parenting on Yahoo! Shine. Is a 2-year-old girl really a flight risk? Of course not, unless she's having a temper tantrum.Colette Vieau and her family were heading home from vacation, when their toddler had a code red melt-down after boarding the plane. Refusing to stay seated and buckled up, and possibly agitating her 3-year-old sister, Vieau's youngest daughter, Natalie, became public enemy number one as the plane crew waited for take off.Related: First-Class Flying Penguins Delight Delta Passengers"We were holding them down with all of our might, seat belt on.
